Combine canola oil, garlic, ginger and red pepper flakes in a non-metal bowl and add shrimp. Refrigerate for about an hour. Heat wok or frying pan over high heat. Add marinade and shrimp and cook 2 -3 minutes until shrimp change to a pinkish color. Remove to a plate. Add canola oil to pan and add snap peas, pepper and onions. Stir-fry about 3 minutes until tender crisp. Return shrimp and juices to pan and stir-fry another minute. Season with salt and pepper and garnish with freshly chopped cilantro and black sesame seeds or toasted sesame seeds. Serve over steamed noodles or with rice.